{"lemma":"جِهادٌ","slug":"جِهادٌ","root":"ج.ه.د","root_slug":"ج-ه-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ه-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جِهاد","root":"جهد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6513","n6517"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَاهَدَ (jāhada) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"struggle, effort","tags":["uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"فَلَا تُطِعِ الْكَافِرِينَ وَجَاهِدْهُم بِهِ جِهَادًا كَبِيرًا","english":"So do not obey the faithless, but wage with it [the Revelation] a great struggle against them."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"religious struggle","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flat land; rugged, hard land","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"desert","tags":["uncountable"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/d͡ʒi.haːd/","/d͡ʒa.haːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6513","headword_ar":"جِهَادٌ","root":"jhd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAhd","text_ar":"جاهد"},{"kind":"text","text":", properly signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"using,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerting, one's utmost power, efforts, endeavours,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability, in contending with an object of disapprobation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is of three kinds, namely, a visible enemy, the devil, and one's self; all of which are included in the term as used in the Kur xxii. 77. (Er-Rághib, TA.) See also 1, first sentence. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAhd AlEaduw~a","text_ar":"جاهد العَدُوَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, A, Mgh,) inf. n. as above (JK, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujaAhadapN","text_ar":"مُجَاهَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fought with the enemy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he encountered the enemy, imposing upon himself difficulty"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerting his power"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"efforts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endeavours"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the utmost thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to repel him, his enemy doing the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAhd","text_ar":"جاهد"},{"kind":"text","text":"came to be used by the Muslims to signify generally"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he fought, warred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waged war, against unbelievers"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAhd fiY sabiyli A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"جاهد فِى سَبِيلِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jihaAdN","text_ar":"جِهَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujaAhadapN","text_ar":"مُجَاهَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fought, &c., in the way of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the cause of religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["JK","A","Mgh","K","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n6517","headword_ar":"جَهَادٌ","root":"jhd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hard land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land in which is no herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard land in which is no herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even, land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rugged land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"also used as an epithet; so that you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN jahaAdN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ جَهَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, smooth land, in which is no hill:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most plain and even of land, whether it have produced herbage or not, not having any mountain or hill near it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such is what is termed a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHoraA='","text_ar":"صَحْرَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an open tract of land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterile, barren,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unfruitful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"land,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is nothing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAdN","text_ar":"جَمَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juhudN","text_ar":"جُهُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AA, L.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, K;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jahaADN","text_ar":"جَهَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","TA","K","ISh","Fr"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"جهاد","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23201#8baf38","body_html":"<span>الجهاد: هو الدعاء إلى الدين الحق.</span>"}]}}